SIMPLE: wetness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wetness
<hw>Wet"ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
quality or state of being wet; moisture; humidity; <as>as, the
<ex>wetness</ex> of land; the <ex>wetness</ex> of a
cloth</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A watery or moist state of the atmosphere; a state
of being rainy, foggy, or misty; <as>as, the <ex>wetness</ex> of weather
or the season</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Wetness</xex> generally implies more water or
liquid than is implied by <xex>humidness</xex> or
<xex>moisture</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Sweat or sweating; -- a euphemism.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wet nurse</ent>⟦br⟧
